<item>
            <title>[LDAP-290] LdapTemplate logs message at INFO level instead of DEBUG when authentication exception is captured</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/LDAP-290</link>
                <project id="10071" key="LDAP">Spring LDAP</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When there is an authentication exception in the method below, a full stack trace is logged at info level; this is polluting the logs whenever a user cannot authenticate. Since the exception is added to the callback object it seems logical that the caller should decide what to do with this exception. Even a DEBUG message seems useless here. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public boolean authenticate(Name base, String filter, String password,&lt;br/&gt;
			final AuthenticatedLdapEntryContextCallback callback, final AuthenticationErrorCallback errorCallback)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
